A threat against flight 826 from Cologne Bonn to Milan 's Malpensa airport was received on Sunday evening .
The threat in Cologne immediately alerted the pilot of the Airbus A320 , which was taxiing toward the runway , Germanwings .
A total of 132 people were aboard the plane , including 126 passengers and crew were evacuated .
Germanwings has been in the spotlight since one of its planes was deliberately crashed into a mountain in the French Alps .